    "explanation": "The two diagrams depict similar software architectures related to a prediction platform built on the Aeternity Blockchain. Both diagrams include common components such as the User, Aeternity Blockchain, PredictionCards Smart Contract, Process Prediction Service, Oracle Service, and IPFS. Diagram 2 provides a more detailed breakdown of the Frontend (using React, Redux, API, and WalletClient) and separates the Backend and External Services into logical groups. Diagram 2 also includes CoinGecko API, detailing the external service needed for data retrieval. Diagram 1 has less granularity, representing the Frontend as a single component and omitting specific backend and external service details.\n\nThe connectors in both diagrams illustrate the interactions between the components. Several common connectors highlight core functionality, such as the Process Prediction Service and Oracle Service interacting with the Aeternity Blockchain. Diagram 2 includes additional connectors showing internal interactions within the Frontend and Backend Services.\n\nIn terms of architectural structure, Diagram 2 provides a clearer layered architecture, with Frontend, Backend, and External Services explicitly grouped. This improves readability and understanding of the system's organization. Diagram 1, while simpler, lacks this layered organization. Diagram 2 also includes annotations listing key functions within the system, enhancing its informative value.\n\nDiagram 2 is clearly the better diagram, as it is far more detailed, specific, and well-organized. The additional detail clarifies the system design, providing better insight into the dataflow between services and clients. The visual clarity is also enhanced with a clearer diagram. The additional information regarding specific technologies (React, Redux) and external APIs is significant and important. For all of these reasons, Diagram 2 is more useful and better depicts the architectural design.\n\n**Score:**\nDiagram 1: 5/10\nDiagram 2: 9/10"
